I(t) ≥ Imin⁡ >0(and optionally I(t)≤Imax⁡<∞ if an upper bound is desired).I(t)\ \ge\ I_{\min}\ >0 \quad (\text{and optionally } I(t)\le I_{\max}<\infty\ \text{if an upper bound is desired}).I(t) ≥ Imin​ >0(and optionally I(t)≤Imax​<∞ if an upper bound is desired).

3. RCR Stability Theorem (ISS & Ultimate Boundedness)
Theorem. Under Axioms 1–4, with k,α,β>0k,\alpha,\beta>0k,α,β>0 and I(t)∈[Imin⁡,Imax⁡]I(t)\in[I_{\min},I_{\max}]I(t)∈[Imin​,Imax​], the residual system is input-to-state stable (ISS) with respect to d(t)d(t)d(t) and is uniformly ultimately bounded (UUB). In particular, if
kα > ε,k\alpha\ >\ \varepsilon,kα > ε,
then there exists a constant ultimate bound
 ∣R(t)∣ ≤ B(ε) := εkβ Imax⁡ for all sufficiently large t.\boxed{\ |R(t)|\ \le\ B(\varepsilon)\ :=\ \frac{\varepsilon}{k\beta}\,I_{\max}\ } \quad \text{for all sufficiently large } t . ∣R(t)∣ ≤ B(ε) := kβε​Imax​ ​for all sufficiently large t.
