3 RCR Stability Theorem (ISS & Ultimate Boundedness)
Theorem 1. Under Axioms 1–4, with k, α, β > 0 and I(t) ∈ [Imin, Imax], the residual system is Inputto-State Stable (ISS) with respect to d(t) and is Uniformly Ultimately Bounded (UUB). In
particular, if
kα > ε,
then there exists a constant ultimate bound
|R(t)| ≤ B(ε) := ε
kβ Imax for all sufficiently large t.
Corollary 1 (Asymptotic Coherence). If policy tightening drives ε → 0 (perfect reciprocity), then
B(ε) → 0 and consequently
R(t) → 0, R˙(t) → 0 as t → ∞,
achieving the Coherence Goal State.
Remark 1 (Sufficiency vs. Necessity). The margin kα > ε is a sufficient dissipativity condition for a
clean linear term; stability is also aided by the intrinsic quadratic damping −kβR2 with β > 0.
